  "title": "AssetFactory",
  "description": "Contract that every asset factory must satisfy. A factory is responsible for two distinct steps: converting a raw HTTP Response into a serialisable intermediate form (`process`), and then turning that intermediate form into the final engine object (`create`). Separating the two steps allows caching layers to persist the processed data and skip the network on subsequent loads.",
